From: Arnaldo Carvalho de Melo <acme@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 15 Oct 2019 12:44:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] tools headers UAPI: Sync sched.h with the kernel
Git-commit: 5eca1379c0eb06e3908179665230a86d19bd2df7
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc5
References: bsc#1164648,jsc#SLE-11493

To get the changes in:

  78f6face5af3 ("sched: add kernel-doc for struct clone_args")
  f14c234b4bc5 ("clone3: switch to copy_struct_from_user()")

This file gets rebuilt, but no changes ensues:

   CC       /tmp/build/perf/trace/beauty/clone.o

This addresses this perf build warning:

  Warning: Kernel ABI header at 'tools/include/uapi/linux/sched.h' differs from latest version at 'include/uapi/linux/sched.h'
  diff -u tools/include/uapi/linux/sched.h include/uapi/linux/sched.h

